Quick Start
bash# 1. Place your regional LLM output in the input file
#    Expected format: persona, region, confidence level

# 2. Generate a review sample
python data_sampling.py

# 3. Audit the sample output
#    Review sampled_output.csv — validate that LLM logic is sound

# 4. Run imputation on validated regions
python impute_region_to_zip.py
#    → Outputs a ZIP-level file ready for activation

What this demonstrates

Practical AI integration: Turning generative AI outputs into structured, production-ready data
Human-in-the-loop design: Quality gate before any LLM-derived data reaches downstream systems
Lightweight architecture: Two focused scripts, no heavy dependencies — easy to adapt or extend



Note: This is a portfolio prototype. Input/output filenames, internal system references, and proprietary data have been removed. The methodology and pipeline structure are illustrative.
